Pudding is a type of food that can be either a dessert or a savoury (salty or spicy) dish that is part of the main meal.

In the United States and Canada, pudding characteristically denotes a sweet, 
milk-based dessert similar in consistency to egg-based custards, instant custards or a mousse, 
often commercially set using cornstarch, gelatin or similar coagulating agent such as Jell-O. 

